properties.name: Call Me Al
properties.description:
Do you always seem to be falling in spectacular fashion? Do you feel the public has drastically underestimated the dangers of land shark attacks? Do you really need to get to Wally World? Or perhaps you have some important tidbits of Zen golfing wisdom you'd like to share?

Well then this may just be the ride for you!

This week, we're looking at 25 miles, with one long hill. It's not super steep for most of the way, but it gets up there; oh, you can be sure of that. What this means, of course, is that we get some really nice views. We also get about 1/2 mile of dirt, some of which you will almost certainly want to walk instead of ride. And this will be just fine because, as we mentioned, you'll have all those pretty views to look at.

And what more could you want from life, really?
